On Fri, Sep 30, 2011 at 7:14 PM, David Saff &lt;david@...&gt; wrote:

&gt; **
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; For this particular problem, you might want to consider:
&gt;
&gt; 1) Create your own subclass of RunListener that does the logging you
&gt; want. Call it MyRunListener
&gt;
&gt; 2) Create your own ClasspathSuite that overrides run like this:
&gt;
&gt; class MyClasspathSuite extends ClasspathSuite {
&gt; // ...
&gt;
&gt; @Override public void run(RunNotifier notifier) {
&gt; notifier.addListener(new MyRunListener());
&gt; super.run(notifier);
&gt; }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; There&#39;s not an off-the-shelf way to add rules to a bunch of tests, but
&gt; in this case, your use case is closer to listening than modification.
&gt;
&gt; Does that help?
&gt;

Yep, thanks, we&#39;ll give it a try.
